                   READY LETWYCHE
               <interp inst="t17861025-65-person895" type="surname" value="READY LETWYCHE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17861025-65-person895" type="given" value="NICHOLAS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17861025-65-person895" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             sworn.</p>
               <p>I examined this with the original affidavit and had it marked; it is a correct office copy, signed Cain O'Hara, Gosport, in the county of Southampton, maketh oath; ten pounds, seven shillings, and eleven pence, for board and lodging, and goods sold and delivered to the said 
               <persName id="t17861025-65-person896">
                  Eleanor
                   Kervin
               <interp inst="t17861025-65-person896" type="surname" value="Kervin"></interp>
